**2. Add memoization to KanbanBoard (`apps/web/src/components/KanbanBoard.tsx`):**

Add useMemo for column grouping:
```typescript
const tasksByColumn = useMemo(() => {
  const map = new Map<string, Task[]>();
  for (const col of columns) map.set(col, []);
  for (const task of tasks) {
    const col = task.sprintColumn || columns[0];
    map.get(col)?.push(task) || map.get(columns[0])?.push(task);
  }
  return map;
}, [tasks, columns]);
```

Add useMemo for blocked status:
```typescript
const blockedTasks = useMemo(() => {
  const blocked = new Set<string>();
  for (const task of tasks) {
    if (!task.dependsOn) continue;
    try {
      const ids = JSON.parse(task.dependsOn) as string[];
      const isBlocked = ids.some(id => {
        const dep = tasks.find(t => t.taskId === id);
        return !dep || dep.status !== "done";
      });
      if (isBlocked) blocked.add(task.taskId);
    } catch {}
  }
  return blocked;
}, [tasks]);
```

Replace inline task filtering in render with map lookups.

